        <x-sections.card-image-with-text
            image="/images/vehicle-magnets/top5pct-car-magnets-truck-magnets-joliet.jpg"
            alt="Custom car magnets and truck magnetic signs printed in Joliet Illinois"
            title="Removable Car Magnets for Business and Personal Vehicles"
        >
            <p class="mb-4">We print custom car magnets and truck magnetic signs for business owners throughout Joliet and Will County who use their personal vehicles for both work and personal use. The biggest advantage of a magnetic vehicle sign is its flexibility. When you are heading to your kid's soccer game or running personal errands on a weekend, you can pull the magnet off in seconds and store it flat in your trunk. When you are back on the job driving to client locations, you snap it back on the door and your vehicle is instantly branded. No permanent commitment, no vinyl residue, just clean removable advertising exactly when you need it.</p>
            <p class="mb-4">Magnetic signs are extremely popular among solo contractors, service professionals, real estate agents, delivery drivers, and small business owners throughout the Chicagoland area. These are people who rely on their personal truck or van for daily business travel but do not want their personal vehicle permanently marked with business graphics. A magnetic sign gives them the best of both worlds. They get the branding and the credibility that comes with a marked vehicle without sacrificing the flexibility of keeping their personal life separate from their business life.</p>
            <p>We have helped hundreds of businesses in Joliet, Shorewood, Rockdale, and across Will County create magnetic signs that look sharp and hold up to daily use. Our magnets are made to stay on your vehicle through highway speeds, wind, and rain. We guarantee our signs will not fly off your vehicle in normal driving conditions when properly applied to a clean, flat metal surface. Give us a call at (815) 349 8600 to order your custom vehicle magnets today.</p>
        </x-sections.card-image-with-text>

        <x-sections.card-image-with-text
            image="/images/vehicle-magnets/top5pct-car-magnets-vehicle-magnets-joliet.jpg"
            alt="Custom full color vehicle magnets and car door magnetic signs printed in Joliet Illinois"
            title="Full Color or Vinyl Cut: Choosing the Right Magnet"
            imagePosition="right"
        >
            <p class="mb-4">We offer two types of magnetic vehicle signs at Top 5 Percent and each one has its own advantages depending on your budget, your design, and how you plan to use the sign. The first type is digitally printed full color magnets. These are the right choice when your design includes photographs, gradients, multiple colors, or complex logo artwork. We print directly onto the magnetic material using high resolution full color printing that produces vivid, sharp results. If your sign will be used outdoors and exposed to weather, we apply a protective overlaminate that seals the print surface and greatly extends the life of your magnet in rain, sun, and heat.</p>
            <p class="mb-4">The second type is vinyl cut magnetic signs. These use a prelaminated opaque vinyl material that we cut into lettering and shapes in up to three colors. Vinyl cut signs are a great choice for simple designs with clear, bold lettering and a clean look. They are also more budget friendly which makes them an excellent option for a small business ordering its first set of vehicle signs or a contractor who needs a basic contact information sign without any complex artwork. Both types produce a professional result and both types use the same heavy duty magnetic base material.</p>
            <p>We carry magnetic signs in three standard sizes to fit different vehicles. The 20 by 10 inch size works well on compact cars and smaller doors. The 24 by 12 inch size fits mid size sedans and most pickup truck doors. The 24 by 18 inch size is best for SUVs, vans, and larger commercial vehicles where you need maximum visibility. We recommend choosing the largest size that fits comfortably on your door panel for the best readability at a distance. Call us at (815) 349 8600 and our team will help you pick the right size and style for your vehicle.</p>
        </x-sections.card-image-with-text>

        <x-sections.card-2image-with-text
            image1="/images/vehicle-magnets/top5pct-business-magnets-car-magnets-joliet.jpg"
            alt1="Custom business car magnets and magnetic vehicle signs printed in Joliet Illinois"
            image2="/images/vehicle-magnets/top5pct-large-magnets-magnets-near-me-joliet.jpg"
            alt2="Large format vehicle magnets and magnetic signs near Joliet Illinois"
            title="30 Mil Thickness, Die Cut Corners, and Weather Resistance"
        >
            <p class="mb-4">Not all vehicle magnets are the same thickness, and thickness matters more than most people realize. Some shops sell 20 mil magnets for vehicle use, but 20 mil magnets are really designed for indoor refrigerator and whiteboard applications. A 20 mil magnet placed on a vehicle door at highway speeds creates significant wind lift risk. At Top 5 Percent, we use 30 mil thick magnetic material for all vehicle applications. The extra thickness gives the magnet a stronger grip on your vehicle door and reduces the risk of the sign shifting or lifting during normal driving. This is not a detail we cut corners on because the last thing we want is for your sign to become a road hazard.</p>
            <p class="mb-4">We also die cut and round all four corners of every vehicle magnet we produce. This is another important detail that most budget magnet shops skip. Square corners on a vehicle magnet act like a scoop at highway speeds. Wind catches the corners and begins to peel the magnet away from the door surface. By rounding all four corners we eliminate the leading edge that wind grabs onto, which significantly reduces the chance of your magnet lifting during travel. Combined with our 30 mil thickness, this means our magnets stay put in conditions that would send a cheaper sign flying down the highway.</p>
            <p>We also provide guidance on proper magnet care because how you maintain your magnet directly affects how long it lasts. You should remove the magnet at least once a week, wipe down the magnet and the vehicle surface with a clean cloth, and reapply to a dry, clean door panel. Never leave a magnet on the vehicle through an automated car wash and avoid placing the magnet over door molding or uneven surfaces. Following these simple steps will keep your magnet looking great and holding strong for years. Contact us at (815) 349 8600 in Joliet to place your order.</p>
        </x-sections.card-2image-with-text>


